values.value: The Contracting Officer's approval does not constitute a determination of the acceptability of the terms or of the allowability of costs, or the allowance of any deviation to the contract or approved management systems, unless the consent or approval specifies otherwise consistent with the Prime Contract Clause H-29.
By granting approval you are validating, to the best of your knowledge, this proposal meets the requirements of Clause H-29 for your area of review.
